rComments: Everyone on here saying she's a tough prof - yeah, but like do your work and go to class and she's great. My favourite thing about Prof Dubois is that she will hear any opinion as long as you argue it well. She direct seminars very well in a way that really encourages class participation. Friendly & helpful outside of class too.
She's tough but a great prof. It's a lot of work upfront but one of my favourite classes! Knows her content well and is passionate about it.

She is the most incompetent professor at the University of Ottawa. She really does not deserve to be there. Her class is an absolute disaster. She is not prepared for the class, messed up the readings, and did not know how to present the material and facilitate discussion. Her expectations are vague and unclear.

Dubois is a good prof but dont skip. Beware of pop quizzes and she only puts up slides at the end of class.  She is a very tough grader so you have to work hard for your mark but she does let you know what will be on the final exam ( short & long questions) Lectures are kinda boring and dont have a real flow to them but she does know her material.

Horrible prof. She's not clear on what she expects out of you. Posts slides after class which is essentially useless. It's better to look up the content on wikipedia and online than rely on her lectures. Her midterm was tricky so beware. She also gives pop quiz at times she knows people will skip. She's also super strict.

This prof is very knowledgable in her field and presents her lectures in a clear and concise way. Always had a chance to discuss current events which helped for the final and midterm. Don't skip many lectures or you will suffer for it. Clear grading criteria, she goes over exactly what to do and not to do many times. Would recommend her.
